main event: Two unidentified objects were spotted near Midway Island on May 27, 1960.
interesting points: The first object appeared to be a large green flare at an altitude of 22,000 feet, visible for about 30 seconds.
Sixty seconds later, another object was sighted on the same course, appearing to be on a horizontal plane and moving at an estimated speed of 1,200 to 1,500 mph.
The weather was clear above 15,000 feet, and there was no air traffic at the time.
The sighting was evaluated as a non-threat, but more information was requested to make a valid conclusion.
Similar objects had been observed before by the witnesses, but details were not provided.
